FBIS4-62348 "drsov094_d_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-094 Daily Report 14 May 1994 Regional Affairs Tatar, Chuvash Presidents Sign Friendship Treaty Tatar, Chuvash Presidents Sign Friendship Treaty LD1405104594 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 0700 GMT 14 May 94 LD1405104594 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service English BFN [Text] The presidents of Tatarstan and neighboring Chuvashia, both making part of the Russian Federation, signed a treaty on friendship and cooperation in Kazan on Friday. Tatar president, Mintimer Shaymiyev, said his republic had more than 100 Chuvash schools, a newspaper published in Chuvash and radio programs. Chuvashia claims similar conditions for ethnic Tatars.
